column5: some more of Lake Simcoe's tasty perch I was just playing with my food not eating them the perch was just playing with my jig too   <iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ZS01SuJPFes" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
that would work  off to the narrows...LOL
I was out there yesterday, we had a fish on almost every cast of varied sizes we were using a pickeral rig with white plastics.
cool they are lots of fun  and a great way to get new fishermen into the sport
I sure hope that was all they were playing with Terry     How come you don't add music to your videos anymore? TJ

yeah I have been spending a lot of time in a motel and the internet is dial up speed, so I am just lucky I can get a 2 minute video uploaded in 24 hours....so doing anything with the video just ain't happening right now..... On the road again
